<item>
            <title>[LU-16197] kfilnd: LNet NID index not mapping to kfi_cxi PID</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16197</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lustre cray-2.15 supports LNet NID types larger than 32-bits. As a part of this change, some of the LNet NID fields are stored in big endian order. kfi_cxi expects things to be in host byte order. kfilnd needs to translate LNet NID nid_num to host byte order. Failing to do this is preventing multiple LNet NID indexes from being used.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
